{
  "message": "fuzz(inode-roundtrip): 9 raw + truncated seeds for parser-only paths\n\nfuzz_inode_roundtrip drives four modes (Raw / SyntheticRegular /\nSyntheticDirectory / Truncated). Existing 4 ad-hoc seeds (raw,\nraw_128, regular, directory) covered the simplest happy paths but\nleft the Raw and Truncated boundary cases unexplored.\n\nAdds 9 seeds that exercise the parser-only paths (Raw + Truncated):\n\n  Raw mode:\n  * 128-byte all-zero raw (smallest legal inode size)\n  * 256-byte all-zero raw (largest typical inode size)\n  * 128-byte raw shaped as a regular file (S_IFREG | 0o644,\n    links_count = 1)\n  * 256-byte raw with extra_isize stamped at offset 0x80\n  * 127-byte raw (one byte short \u2014 must be rejected)\n  * 200-byte raw (between 128 and 256 \u2014 exercises the\n    \"size-class detection picks 128\" branch)\n\n  Truncated mode (raw input then truncate-length selector):\n  * truncate to 0 (empty input \u2014 parser early-returns)\n  * truncate to 127 (one byte short of the smallest legal size)\n  * \"no truncation effect\" \u2014 selector >= raw length keeps full\n    payload\n\nThe synthetic-mode seeds I originally drafted (seed_synth_regular_*\nand seed_synth_dir_*) are deliberately omitted: each one drives the\nharness's fuzz_serialize_inode \u2192 parse_from_bytes round-trip and\nfires `std::process::abort()` on non-trivial inode geometries \u2014 a\ngenuine pre-existing roundtrip mismatch in the synthetic builder\nthat also affects the existing `seed_raw` corpus entry. Triaging\nthat mismatch is left for a follow-up audit; this commit lands the\nraw/truncated coverage that is independent of the bug.\n\nValidated by libFuzzer over the 9 new seeds in isolation: 10 runs,\nno crashes, coverage rose to 286 PCs / 355 features.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
